Advanced Tobacco ProductsInc said it signed a letter of intent to license a smokingdeterrent product to a unit of Pharmacia AB &lt;PHABY> of Sweden.    Under terms of the agreement, the company said Pharmacia'sAB Leo unit will pay an undisclosed sum, includingnon-refundable royalties, for exclusive rights to evaluateAdvanced Tobacco's nicotine technology through July.    The company said the unit will also have an option to buyexclusive worldwide licensing rights for the technology foradditional cash and royalties. Reuter&#3;